          <fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>The corrected counit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ' \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex> is defined like so:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \epsilon ' x :\equiv 
  \epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
^{-1} \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \epsilon  x
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>The coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon '\circ  f]]></fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001V.xml" title="naturality of homotopies" addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001W.xml" title="naturality of homotopies onto the identity" addr="forest://erct/erct-001W" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001W" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
