 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x, \epsilon  x\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, and the required paths can be constructed via the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001R.xml" title="path object structure on fibers" addr="forest://erct/erct-001R" type="local">univalence principle for fibers</fr:link> using the unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  f^{-1}\circ  f = 1_{A}]]></fr:tex>, the coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex>, and the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001V.xml" title="naturality of homotopies" addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" type="local">naturality of homotopies</fr:link>.</html:p>
